                <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Gaviarius <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>epos</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>aug</abbr><ex>ur</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Iulius Caes<lb break="no" n="3"/>aris <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibertus</ex></expan> Meges <expan><abbr>IIvir</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>quinque</abbr><ex>nnales</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>murum ex <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecreto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecurionum</ex></expan> reficiundum <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>uraverunt</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/>i&amp;lt;s&amp;gt;demque probaverunt <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>onstat</ex></expan> HS ||(quattuor milium)CC
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Weitere Inschrift von Gaviarius und Meges: AE 1982, 765. Z. 5 (Ende): hinter HS Zahlzeichen für 1000 und Zahlzeichen für 3000.</p>
            </div>
